<p>A U.S. Navy helicopter and a fighter jet went down in separate incidents while operating from the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz in the South China Sea on Sunday; all crew were rescued and are in stable condition, the Navy said . The Navy described both events as occurring during routine operations and said investigations are underway to determine causes . The crashes happened during a high-profile U.S. presence in the region and prompted a public response from Beijing, which said frequent U.S. deployments are a “root cause” of maritime security problems while offering humanitarian assistance if asked .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/OrVYmWLMFQ-is9yiuTp4XjPDnVyAawJ4hqIxwhjOho5iq8TH89xsOXV6TEjBPQllZMAdlQYbrK_fxhWbpx03SzOoV1RTSkPf7IzD55ccNTTkJfZfk4gtThTJjwYxQJS3I8ROpKCZcBgTtVGcso1Jx3neyxgvDEeQ7gCQG5Hu0qtSFXTE' alt='A MH-60R Sea Hawk on the flight deck of the U.S.S. Ronald Reagan in the South China Sea in 2020; the same model went down on Sunday.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Aircraft specifics: The downed aircraft were identified as an MH-60R Sea Hawk (three crew) and an F/A-18F Super Hornet (two crew), and both crews were recovered alive</li><li>Timing details: The two accidents occurred roughly 30 minutes apart while both aircraft were operating from USS Nimitz, according to U.S. Navy statements</li><li>Beijing response: China’s foreign ministry blamed frequent U.S. deployments for maritime security problems and said Beijing would be &#x27;willing to provide assistance to the US from a humanitarian perspective&#x27; if asked</li><li>Recent precedent: News reports note an earlier 2025 incident in which two U.S. warplanes were lost from the carrier USS Harry S. Truman, highlighting recent carrier operational mishaps this year</li></ul><blockquote>All personnel involved are safe and in stable condition. - U.S. Navy</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>U.S. Navy / Pentagon: The Navy said both aircraft went down while conducting routine operations from the USS Nimitz, that all crew were recovered and that investigations into the causes are underway. (<a href='https://www.cnn.com/2025/10/26/politics/navy-aircraft-crash-south-china-sea'>CNN</a>)</li><li>Chinese foreign ministry: Beijing said frequent U.S. military deployments in the South China Sea are the &#x27;root cause&#x27; of maritime security problems and offered humanitarian assistance to the U.S. if requested. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/military/article/3330434/us-navy-helicopter-and-warplane-crash-south-china-sea-same-day'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/27/world/asia/navy-aircraft-crash-south-china-sea.html'>2 U.S. Navy Aircraft Go Down in South China Sea</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/china/military/article/3330434/us-navy-helicopter-and-warplane-crash-south-china-sea-same-day'>Beijing accuses US of undermining South China Sea peace after twin air crashes</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-27/us-navy-aircraft-crashes-south-china-sea/105938082'>Two US Navy aircraft crash within 30 minutes in South China Sea</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/united-states/us-navy-helicopter-jet-crash-into-south-china-sea'>US Navy helicopter, jet crash into South China Sea in separate incidents on same day</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951562/us-navy-helicopter-jet-crash-into-south-china-sea'>US Navy helicopter, jet crash into South China Sea</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/inthenews/comments/1oh9ttt/navy_loses_two_aircraft_from_uss_nimitz_aircraft/'>Navy loses two aircraft from USS Nimitz aircraft carrier within 30 minutes</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/us-navy-helicopter-fighter-jet-crash-in-south-china-sea-probe-underway-13945310.html'>US Navy helicopter, fighter jet crash in South China Sea, probe underway</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cnn.com/2025/10/26/politics/navy-aircraft-crash-south-china-sea'>In separate incidents, an MH-60R Seahawk helicopter and an F/A-18F Super Hornet fighter jet of the United States Navy, operating off of the aircraft carrier USS Nimitz, crash in the South China Sea. All crew of both craft are rescued.</a> - cnn.com</li></ul>